HEADWORD: Malpighia
<hw>Mal*pi"ghi*a</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL. See
<er>Malpighian</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A genus of tropical
American shrubs with opposite leaves and small white or reddish flowers.
The drupes of <spn>Malpighia glabra</spn> (formerly <spn>Malpighia
urens</spn>) are eaten under the name of <prod>Barbadoes
cherries</prod>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Malpighiaceous</ent>⟦br⟧
